sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Platform Admin
    participant Dashboard as odh-dashboard<br/>(maas BFF)
    participant MaaS as MaaS Controller
    participant AIGateway as AI Gateway<br/>Payload Processing
    participant Authorino as Kuadrant/Authorino
    participant Envoy as Envoy Gateway
    participant MaaSAPI as maas-api
    participant ExtProvider as External LLM Provider<br/>(OpenAI/Anthropic/Azure)
    participant Client as API Consumer

    Note over Admin,Client: Workflow 5: Models as a Service (External LLM Providers)

    %% Admin setup
    Admin->>Dashboard: Configure external model provider
    Dashboard->>MaaS: Create MaaSModelRef +<br/>MaaSAuthPolicy + MaaSSubscription CRs

    MaaS->>Envoy: Create HTTPRoutes for model endpoints
    MaaS->>Authorino: Create AuthPolicies<br/>(API key validation)
    MaaS->>Authorino: Create RateLimitPolicies
    MaaS->>MaaSAPI: Deploy maas-api service

    AIGateway->>AIGateway: ExternalModel/ExternalProvider<br/>controllers reconcile
    AIGateway->>AIGateway: Create Istio ServiceEntry +<br/>DestinationRule (TLS origination)

    %% Client request flow
    Client->>Envoy: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>(HTTPS/443, API key header)

    Envoy->>Envoy: ext_proc: payload-pre-processing<br/>(extract model name from body)
    Envoy->>Authorino: Validate API key
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: Callback: verify subscription
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Subscription valid
    Authorino-->>Envoy: Auth OK + rate limit check

    Envoy->>Envoy: ext_proc: payload-processing<br/>(inject provider credentials,<br/>translate API format if needed)

    Envoy->>ExtProvider: Forward to provider<br/>(HTTPS/443, TLS origination,<br/>provider API key injected)
    ExtProvider-->>Envoy: Provider response
    Envoy-->>Client: Response (HTTPS)
